latestIgtvVideos.title: #StylingSeshwithSim Ep #24 Big Little Lies Style Re-creation
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
How many of you have loved the series Big Little Lies? I know I have! I’ve been watching reruns of this engaging drama. 

The show is about 5 women who are completely different from each other but are somehow connected by a tragic episode that turns their lives upside down. 
Let’s not even get started about the stellar star cast! I mean you can’t go wrong with the likes of Reese Witherspoon, Nicole Kidman sharing screen space! 
Also, what I loved about the series is how each character’s style also defines their personality to a large extent and that is what I’ve tried to recreate here. 
I sincerely hope you guys like the re-creations. Please watch the video and do share your thoughts with me! ❤️

1. @reesewitherspoon as Madeline: Feminine with Florals dominating her style sensibilities.
2. @nicolekidman as Celeste: Classy and Understated with muted tones. 
3. @zoeisabellakravitz as Bonnie: Bohemian with a lot of earthy tones accessorised by a lot of beads and stones. 
4. @lauradern as Renata: The character is synonymous with Power dressing. Classy and structured. 
5. @shailenewoodley as Jane: Basics define her style. Jane doesn't want to stand out, but would rather blend in.

Song credits: Cold Little Heart Radio edit by @michaelkiwanuka (@biglittlelies soundtrack)

(Un)Blending in the city that makes dreams come true! #desiInfluencer
As part of my Entrepreneur project, I had to create a business model that I truly believe in. If you know me by now, you know I wear my roots on my sleeves! I chose a service based model that provides small to mid-level South Asian fusion wear brands a global platform. For someone who phases out seeing numbers, this course taught me how to calculate P&L, AOV, how to present pitch decks and so much more! This video is a teaser for the project. With just a few days left for the final submission and my video not even close to execution, my anxiety hit through the roof! That is when @byanushkabohra became my saviour! 🫶🏻 She understood my vision with an ease only seasoned artists can! Thank you so much Anushka for helping me out. It truly means a lot. And I ofcourse have to thank @chandeepsodhi who bore the brunt of my panic attacks and hand held me through this semester! 😅
Also, it was so nostalgic to be shooting on the streets after so long! Reminded me of my shoot days in Bombay! 
Hope you guys like this video as much as we enjoyed making it. 🥰
Outfit details (So proud to be flaunting these homegrown labels 🤍)

Black velvet blouse- @rishitamitali_

Story time- I remember as a kid, watching my mom head to work every morning draped in her graceful handloom cotton taant saris—effortlessly elegant, no matter the season. In winter, she’d layer them with cozy cardigans, making me wonder how she always looked so beautifully put together.

Styling this simplistic yet elegant ombré linen sari from @ilovepaeony brought back those cherished memories, taking me on a nostalgic ride back to those mornings filled with awe and admiration for her timeless style.
